A devastating car bomb attack at the Hilton hotel in Taba, near the Israel-Egypt border, killed or wounded over 100 people, including at least 23 Israelis.
Additional explosions in tourist camps in the Sinai Peninsula resulted in more casualties.
Israeli officials suspected Hamas involvement, coinciding with Jewish holidays.
Despite warnings, many Israelis continued to visit Sinai, prompting evacuation efforts post-attacks.
Confusion initially surrounded the cause of the blasts, with conflicting reports from Egyptian and Israeli sources.
The tragic events underscored the ongoing security challenges in the region.
